# Generated & lint-gated markdown — Prettier must not reformat these, or it
# desyncs the generators/linters that own their exact bytes.
#
# Every SCHEMA.md is a Pyramid Schema contract owned by tools/schema_lint.py;
# projects/SCHEMA.md is regenerated by tools/gen-projects-schema.py and
# byte-compared by the drift gate (check h). See docs/SCHEMA-FRAMEWORK.md.
SCHEMA.md

# README.md carries the <!-- AUTO:projects --> span generated by
# .github/scripts/dash-gen (drift gate's stale-README check).
/README.md

# Never descend into submodules from the root repo — each is its own repo with
# its own formatting lifecycle (committed there first, per CLAUDE.md).
projects/*/

# Jekyll/Liquid pages — Prettier's markdown parser doesn't understand {% %}
# tags and merges them into prose, which breaks the rendered dash (e.g. it
# collapses a {% for %} loop body onto one line). The dash collection is
# prose-unwrapped by the Liquid-safe tools/unwrap-prose.py instead, wired as a
# pre-commit hook. See .pre-commit-config.yaml.
/index.md
pages/
